  "number": "2.2",
  "title": "Linearity",
  "body": "Linearity     After this section, you will be able to ...    Identify if a differential equation is linear or nonlinear.  Identify a specific nonlinear term in a differential equation.  Anything else?    WRITE SOME INTRODUCTORY TEXT...  Every differential equation is also either linear or nonlinear .   A differential equation is said to be linear if it can be written as    This definition is intended to represent the form of all possible linear differential equations, so it may seem a bit overwhelming. It may be easier to understand linearity based on what it is not, rather than what it is. So, let's begin by describing characteristics of a DE that make it nonlinear.   Identifying a nonlinear DE  A differential equation is nonlinear if any of the following are true about the dependent variable and\/or its derivatives:    Has a power other than 1.     Example:    is nonlinear because the dependent variable, , is raised to the second power.     Is inside another function.    Example:   is nonlinear since the derivative, , is inside a logarithmic function.     Are multiplied together.    Example:   is nonlinear since the first term is a product of and .    Edit Notes:  PERHAPS END WITH A PARAGRAPH STATING THAT THERE ARE MORE WAYS TO CLASSIFY DES AND THAT WE HAVE JUST MENTIONED A FEW?  Greg Comment: Are there really only 2 types of DEs we want to discuss here? How about non\/homogeneous? Did we decide on this?  Greg Comment: I like the idea of showing what a linear equation is not . Can we do more to say what it is? I have in mind something like ``It's a function of x times a derivative of y, plus a function of x times a derivative of y, etc.     Test your Understanding  Let's now look at an example of a linear differential equation.   Determine if the following differential equation is linear. .   This equation is almost in the form (with ) . We just need to make a minor adjustment to see all the parts explicity, where (matching with )     Now you Try The differential equation, , is  Linear   Yes! This DE is linear.    Non-Linear  No, Try again.     Linearity    For each of the following differential equations, identify the independent and dependent variables, the order, and whether it is linear or nonlinear. If nonlinear, give one term in the expression that breaks the linearity.      independent variable:   dependent variable:   2nd order  linear      independent variable:   dependent variable:   3rd order  nonlinear, term:       independent variable:   dependent variable:   4th order  linear      independent variable:   dependent variable:   2nd order  nonlinear, term:       independent variable:   dependent variable:   2nd order  nonlinear, term:       independent variable:   dependent variable:   2nd order  nonlinear, term: or       independent variable:   dependent variable:   3rd order  linear      independent variable:   dependent variable:   2nd order  nonlinear, term:       independent variable:   dependent variable:   1st order  nonlinear, term:       independent variable:   dependent variable:   2nd order  linear      independent variable:   dependent variable:   1st order  linear      independent variable:   dependent variable:   1st order  nonlinear, term:       "
